ENUGU – Less than 24 hours before the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) primary election, the Governor of old Anambra State, Cheif Jim Nwobodo says Peter Mba is the best person to succeed the Enugu State governor, Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi. He said Peter Mba, who is currently running for the governorship election from Nkanu East under PDP is the best man that will provide good governance in the state. Chief Nwobodo’s declaration came after months of speculations on who will succeed Governor Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi in 2023. -Advertisement- Addressing a press conference in Enugu on Tuesday, Chief Nwobodo, a chieftain of PDP in the state said he brought Mba to join the governorship race due to his experience and antecedent in the private sector saying Mba will deliver dividends of democracy to the people He said “we believe that power should rotate to all senatorial districts in the state in order to sustain the peace that our amiable Governor has established in the state already. “I brought Peter Mba to succeed Ugwuanyi because I knew there is an understanding among the people of the state that governorship should rotate among the three senatorial zones and because Nkanu East is backward in terms of development hence the need to consider them. “Secondly, I was looking for somebody who can develop the state, the way it was, when I left it and in October 2019, to be specific, I invited him to my house and told him to consider running for a position as the governor of Enugu and he came back to me after some weeks and consider to run,”. Chief Nwobodo who expressed optimism that Mba will consolidate with Ugwuanyi’s achievements in bringing stability and peace to the state appealed to PDP delegates to support Mba as PDP primary election holds on Wednesday. POLL Chief Nwobodo who lamented over the incessant killings in the country as a result of insecurity said there is no society can witness development in a state of instability and insecurity saying “ so I want to assure the people of the state that we are going into this election as a United family and not as a divided group. He appealed to Ike Ekweremadu and his supporters to join hands with the party leadership and support Mba to emerge as the flag bearer of the party in Enugu state. He said the Former Senate President who is also a gubernatorial aspirant under PDP had come to see him many times and he pleaded with him “to support the peace we are enjoying in the state and withdraw all cases from the court “I have asked Ekweremadu to withdraw all court cases because we need peace in Enugu state so we all must join hands together to bring peace and development in the state,” he said